{opt bootstrap} specifies that posterior estimates of model parameters be 
obtained using sampling with replacement; that is, posterior estimates are
estimated from a bootstrap sample.  The default is to sample the estimates from
the posterior distribution of model parameters or from the large-sample normal
approximation of the posterior distribution.  This option is useful when
asymptotic normality of parameter estimates is suspect.
